There once was a time when American workers loved nothing more than to celebrate the end of a hard day's graft by blowing the froth off a few cold beers.

Just two decades ago beer was by far the most popular alcoholic drink across the country.

But now trouble is brewing in the beer business as Americans appear to be turning their backs on ale for a more refined taste of wine... and bottled water.

