A new report by Gallup has revealed that in the last 20 years, per capita beer consumption has plummeted across the US by 20 per cent.

In its place, wine, tea and liquor have enjoyed a bumper decade while milk, soft drinks and juice are increasingly being left at the back of the fridge.

But the runaway success over the last ten years is bottled water as health-conscious Americans battle to live longer and look better.

